tweet_raw: What is DePIN and how does it work on Solana?DePIN stands for Decentralized Physical Infrastructure Network. These networks scale demand and supply via the network effect a phenomenon where the value of a product increases with the number of users.Summary:- Earn rewards for deploying and maintaining infrastructure- Tokens drive demand and supply through a burn-mint equilibrium- Solana streamlines fair incentive distribution to contributors- Helium ShdwDrive Grass and Hivemapper case studiesDePIN operates by establishing a decentralized ecosystem on the blockchain where stakeholders can participate in the deployment management and governance of physical infrastructure.Projects such as Helium ShdwDrive Grass and Hivemapper use Solana to distribute incentives for providing network resources. Solanaâ€™s composability allows networks to decentralize their ecosystem with a token. The goal is to increase coverage and gain users with the incentive token gaining value and liquidity as the network grows.Helium: The Peopleâ€™s NetworkHelium provides network coverage with decentralized wireless infrastructure. Users deploy hotspots earning IOT and MOBILE tokens in return for providing coverage for the respective subnetworks. The networks quick expansion to nearly 1 million hotspots deployed worldwide exemplifies how network growth is driven by real-world utility.Helium Improvement Proposal (HIP) 87: Proportional Service Provider Rewards proposed to set a fair and sustainable burn-mint equilibrium (BME) for the MOBILE Token. BME aligns token supply with network usage creating a self-regulating economic model to balance the creation and removal of tokens from circulation. Hotspots providing 5G coverage are rewarded with MOBILE at a 1:1 ratio to burned Data Credits (DC). In short the rewards are distributed proportionally to network usage incentivizing the utilization of network resources.ShdwDrive: Decentralized File StorageShdwDrive is an example of a decentralized storage provider. Instead of using a central storage provider shdwNodes contribute storage through the on-chain storage device layer incentivizing node uptime and storage capacity with emission rewards. ShdwDrive creates an economy where SHDW facilitates the provision and usage of storage space. As the demand for decentralized storage grows infrastructure will scale with the network incentivizing shdwNodes to increase storage capacity.Grass: Sharing Unused BandwidthGrass is an app for people to sell their unused internet bandwidth to earn passive income. Through Grass buyers can utilize the bandwidth for research and training AI. Users earn Grass Points during the beta phase which will be converted into network stakes after the beta. Grass Points are rewarded based on uptime measured based on the amount of time a device is connected and actively contributing bandwidth to the network.Running Grass on phones with 24/7 uptime will amplify the network effect increasing the number of active nodes and the value of the network. Currently the only place to download the Grass mobile app is the Solana Saga dApp Store making Saga the only mobile device capable of earning passive income from contributing bandwidth to the network. Grass helps people earn passive income on their phones presenting an opportunity for mobile users to participate in DePIN.Hivemapper: Crowdsourced Data CollectionHivemapper is a project where the community maps the world through crowdsourced data. The primary contribution method is to install a dashcam to collect visual and roadside data while driving providing coverage and fresh data.Participants are incentivized with the HONEY token on Solana. Rewards for popular mapping routes will decrease as saturation increases incentivizing drivers to map low-saturation areas. The dynamic incentive model encourages drivers to collect useful data and earn more HONEY. Map data users burn HONEY to consume data and an equal number of tokens is added back as Map Consumption Rewards following the BME model.ConclusionThe future of DePIN is built by decentralized communities around the world onboarding users to create value and drive demand and supply. From wireless network coverage to monetizing unused resources the decentralized model makes infrastructure scalable by lowering the barrier to entry for providers. Building scalable transparent and rewarding DePIN communities is only possible on Solana.Out of the DePIN projects on Solana which one is your favorite? Bonus points if you can explain how Metcalfeâ€™s Law applies to scaling DePIN networks.

tweet_raw: Aevo: The DeFi SuperApp> What if you could seamlessly trade perpetual contracts options and prelaunch tokens on a one-stop derivatives trading platform that utilizes its own L2-rollup chain?> The answer is @aevoxyz > lets dive in! ðŸ“–â€” TL; DRâ†’ Aevo emerges as a pioneering force in the decentralized finance (DeFi) landscape introducing a high-performance derivatives exchange platform that specializes in derivative products such as options and perpetual contracts.â†’ Aevo offers a range of derivative products including the Prelaunch Market. This market allows traders to speculate on tokens that have not yet been officially launched.â†’ The precision of price forecasts for Aevo Prelaunch tokens is exceptionally high which has earned it the moniker predictor of prelaunch tokens.References: nitter.net/pangestu_karon/sâ€¦â†’  At its core Aevo utilizes its customized Layer-2 roll-up technology called Aevo Chain which is based on the @Optimism Stack and supported by @conduitxyzâ†’This innovative approach allows Aevo to offer an off-chain order book with on-chain settlements.â†’ This hybrid approach ensures high-speed trading without compromising security or decentralization as well as innovative DeFi Derivatives products.â†’ With its own chain Aevo chain significantly improves transaction efficiency and ensures robust access security linked to the Ethereum mainnet.â†’ Aevo Chain L2 will be developed into a comprehensive ecosystem with a focus on speculation-based protocol/ products.â€” Aevo QuickRecap One Pagerâ€” How Aevo Worksâ—¢  Prior to placing any order Aevos off-chain risk engine thoroughly assesses the order against the margin requirements associated with the account. â—¢  This proactive risk assessment guarantees that each account regardless of whether its Standard Margin or Portfolio Margin possesses adequate margin to execute the order successfully.â—¢  The liquidation process on the exchange occurs when an account breaches set requirements leading to forceful cancellation of open orders incremental liquidation of short positions potential trading with the insurance fund and automatic deleveraging if necessary. â—¢  This crucial step plays a vital role in upholding the integrity of the platform and safeguarding user funds. â—¢  Aevoâ€™s  off-chain order book empowers users to post maker and taker orders which are matched off-chain. Only when a successful match is identified Aevos smart contracts residing on our Layer 2 (L2) roll-up execute these orders on-chain.â€” The L2 of Derivativesâ—¢ The Aevo Rollup is EVM-based Ethereum optimistic roll-up OP Stack â—¢ Aevo collaborates closely with Conduit to operate a sequencer.â—¢ This sequencers role is to group transactions together before sending them to the Ethereum Mainnet. â—¢ This process ensures efficient and secure transaction processing while also reducing dispute resolution time. As a result Aevo becomes more responsive and reliable.â—¢ We may also witness the development of potential projects or products utilizing Aevo as the main yield product similar to what we have observed in other derivatives platforms. This further strengthens the Aevo ecosystem.â€” Aevo ExchangeAs the time of writing Aevo has launched several products in their platform:â—¢ PerpetualsAevo offers perpetual contracts for crypto trading allowing traders to speculate on future prices. These contracts have no expiry date and provide leverage for going long or short. They are marked to market and closely track the underlying asset price. Over 50 crypto assets are currently supported.â—¢ OptionsAevo introduces a decentralized platform for trading options providing traders with the tools to hedge against price volatility or speculate on future price movements of cryptocurrencies.â—¢ $aeUSDaeUSD is an ERC-4626 asset on Aevo L2. It combines USDC and sDAI and offers a 4.75% annual percentage yield (APY) for exchange margin with a 100% collateral factor. The purpose of aeUSD is to make trading easier and provide a stable means of exchange on the platform.â—¢ OTC DesksAevos OTC platform addresses the need for large volume trades without impacting the market price significantly.â—¢ PrelaunchesAevos pre-launch token futures allow traders to speculate on the price of tokens before they are officially launched. Currently in Aevo there are three prelaunch markets: @pixels_online / $PIXEL  @Blast_L2 / $BLAST  and @StarkWareLtd / $STARK.â—¢ Vault StrategyAevos vault strategy is designed to optimize returns for participants through automated strategiesâ€” Aevo Farming Programâ—¢  Aevos Farming Program and Airdrop for $AEVO tokens will encourage users to actively participate in the Aevo Exchange. â—¢ By focusing on volume fees and loyalty this program will serve as an incentive for users to engage with the platform.â—¢  The latest collaboration farming program with @Pandora_ERC404  introduces a Farm Boost program. â—¢ Users can enhance their $AEVO airdrop through trading with boosts ranging from 1x to 100x. This program incorporates rarity for additional benefits over a two-week period.â€” Future Aevo L2 Ecosystemâ—¢  Aevo Chain not only offers traders a robust DeFi infrastructure and the best UI/UX but it also empowers other projects to seamlessly develop within the thriving Aevo ecosystem.â€”  Tagged some people that interested on @aevoxyz L2  ecosystem to review:> @Arthur_0x > @TheCryptoDog > @santiagoroel > @adamscochran > @thedefiedge > @Defi_Maestro > @laurashin > @nosleepjon > @OlimpioCrypto > @ZeMariaMacedo > @DoveyWan > @Dogetoshi > @hosseeb > @MustStopMurad > @defi_mochi > @TheDeFiInvestor > @ZoomerOracle > @0xShual > @ThorHartvigsen > @MoonOverlord > @Evan_ss6 > @NTmoney > @litocoen > @LouisCooper_

heterogeneous state by abandoning sharding in favor of supporting various forms and types of l2 therefore in the near future we will observe a multitude of appspecific l2 instead of multiple copies of l2 evm thus ethereum will now try to catch up with the current state of polkadot a state not just a multichain network but also heterogeneous by the nature of segments  from current observations i will share a couple of notes about what i like today in polkadot relative to ethereum l2 implementations   architecture collator  paravalidator  validatorfinalizers ethereum only has a role like collator and it is discussed in the topic decentralized sequencer  native data availability check mechanism when checking a block from collators paravalidators sow data into the internal data availability service and the validatorfinalizers separately check the availability of data before sealing the block ethereums data availability is hot right now but the architecture of solutions should be studied in practice closer to summer  xcm i consider crosschain transactions one of the most magical features of polkadot if polkadot can connect not through hrmp but directly parachains without a link with the relay chain it can turn out very cool the question of linking ethereum l2 segments i remember gavins presentation from copenhagen with embassies in the runtimes of parachains moving in the same direction creating a multichain heterogeneous network to service the world computer
tweet_raw: Polkadot #Parachain or Ethereum #L2?By the beginning of 2024 I can state the fact that the issue of Ethereums development towards a multi-chain network has received a more or less clear trajectory. What has not been for the last 5 years but only meant that Ethereum is waiting for #shardingâ€¦Now I see that eth is not just starting to implement sharding but is striving to achieve a heterogeneous state by abandoning sharding in favor of supporting various forms and types of L2. Therefore in the near future we will observe a multitude of App-specific L2 instead of multiple copies of L2 EVM. Thus Ethereum will now try to catch up with the current state of Polkadot; a state not just a multi-chain network but also heterogeneous by the nature of segments.From current observations I will share a couple of notes about what I like today in Polkadot relative to Ethereum L2 implementations:- Architecture collator > para-validator > validator-finalizers. Ethereum only has a role like collator and it is discussed in the topic Decentralized #Sequencer- Native data availability check mechanism. When checking a block from collators para-validators sow data into the internal Data Availability Service. And the validator-finalizers separately check the availability of data before sealing the block. Ethereums Data Availability is hot right now but the architecture of solutions should be studied in practice closer to summer.- XCM. I consider cross-chain transactions one of the most magical features of Polkadot. If Polkadot can connect not through HRMP but directly parachains without a link with the Relay Chain it can turn out very cool! The question of linking Ethereum L2 segments. I remember Gavins presentation from Copenhagen with embassies in the runtimes of parachains but we are waiting for implementation.But still its interesting personally - two projects very close to me are trying their own ways but whatever they do separately both Ethereum and Polkadot are moving in the same direction creating a multi-chain heterogeneous network to service the world computer.

tweet_text: parallelized evms  sei v2  note this article is divided into two parts and it is also written in longform content   parallelized evms   the ethereum blockchain is central to the decentralized finance defi landscape prompting the development of numerous solutions aimed at addressing scalability issues   the scalability issue which is caused  from the sequential execution of txns on the blockchain has been addressed through the implementation of parallelization in the ethereum layer  parallelized evms are said to be advanced version of traditional evms which allows multiple txns to be processed at the same time making the execution of txn more faster and cheaper   txns are done sequentially on the traditional evm models meaning txn b will only go through after txn a which is the major reason txns processing are slow and fees are insanely high when there is large volume of txns   while in parallelized evms instead of txns to be another one after other multiple txns can be processed at once meaning txn a and txn b are processed at the same time removing the fcfs process which makes the chain very much faster and reducing the gas fees   a good illustration by alibertayen   assuming a block in the eth blockchain contains the following 3 txns   txn a alice sends 5 eth to bob  txn b a sc executes a function to calculate and distribute tokens to various holders based on their current holdings  txn c charlie sends 3 eth to dana  in a standard evm transactions lets assume abc in terms of fees paid are processed sequentially a first the c   in a parallel evm independent transactions like a and c can be processed simultaneously as they dont affect each other   transaction b a smart contract execution possibly dependent on blockchain state may be processed separately   here are some key aspects of parallelized evm   optimistic parallelization the most common approach transactions run in parallel and conflicts are resolved later this ensures determinism while achieving parallel processing benefits   limited scope only transactions not reading or writing the same data can be parallelized however even partial parallelization can significantly improve performance   security parallelization introduces complexities that need careful design and implementation to maintain security  although parallelization of the ethereum layer is a promising approach to solving ethereum blockchain scalability issues it still faces challenges such as technical complexity and ecosystem compatibility however i believe these challenges will be addressed as the narrative continues to develop much like the modular narrative  references datawalletcomcryptoparall mediumcomdoyunkim3878co mediumcomalibertaysolakw
tweet_raw: â—¢ Parallelized EVMs & Sei V2Note: {This article is divided into two parts and it is also written in long-form content}â¯ Parallelized EVMs The Ethereum blockchain is central to the decentralized finance (DeFi) landscape prompting the development of numerous solutions aimed at addressing scalability issues. The scalability issue which is caused  from the Sequential Execution of txns on the blockchain has been addressed through the implementation of Parallelization in the Ethereum layer.Parallelized EVMs are said to be advanced version of traditional EVMs which allows multiple txns to be processed at the same time making the execution of txn more faster and cheaper. Txns are done sequentially on the traditional EVM models meaning â€œtxn Bâ€ will only go through after â€œtxn Aâ€ which is the major reason txns processing are slow and fees are insanely high when there is large volume of txns. While in Parallelized EVMs instead of txns to be another one after other multiple txns can be processed at once meaning â€œtxn Aâ€ and â€œtxn Bâ€ are processed at the same time removing the fcfs process which makes the chain very much faster and reducing the gas fees.â–º A Good Illustration by @alibertayEN â€œAssuming a block in the ETH Blockchain contains the following 3 txns: * Txn A: Alice sends 5 ETH to Bob.* Txn B: A SC executes a function to calculate and distribute tokens to various holders based on their current holdings.* Txn C: Charlie sends 3 ETH to Dana.In a standard EVM transactions (lets assume A>B>C in terms of fees paid) are processed sequentially: A first the C. In a Parallel EVM independent transactions like A and C can be processed simultaneously as they dont affect each other. Transaction B a smart contract execution possibly dependent on blockchain state may be processed separately.â€â–º Here are some key aspects of parallelized EVM:â€¢ Optimistic parallelization: The most common approach. Transactions run in parallel and conflicts are resolved later. This ensures determinism while achieving parallel processing benefits.â€¢ Limited scope: Only transactions not reading or writing the same data can be parallelized. However even partial parallelization can significantly improve performance.â€¢ Security: Parallelization introduces complexities that need careful design and implementation to maintain security.Although parallelization of the Ethereum layer is a promising approach to solving Ethereum blockchain scalability issues it still faces challenges such as technical complexity and ecosystem compatibility. However I believe these challenges will be addressed as the narrative continues to develop much like the Modular narrative.References: datawallet.com/crypto/parallâ€¦medium.com/@doyun.kim3878/coâ€¦medium.com/@alibertaysolak/wâ€¦

tweet_raw: Definitely worth a watch of @CredibleCryptos breakdown of $XRP.He discusses his thoughts in depth of $XRP / $BTC $XRP / $ETH and touches on $XRP / $USD.Key take aways; - We may have slightly further to consolidate. - Looking for Bullish divergence on the 3 day RSI. - Upside moves happen super quickly for $XRP probably all done in a month. - Upside moves can be a significant out performance (as seen below). - Could explode at any point if $BTC continues its move up and $XRP out performs it leads to massive price appreciation so he is positioning for this potential.My thoughts;We have talked about $XRP / $BTC numerous times very similar to what Cred is talking about here.Crypto specifically $XRP is reflexive.When price starts to increase people will become bullish leading to further price increase and more people coming bullish (cycle continues). This can happen extremely quickly with $XRP because crypto is negatively biased towards $XRP for whatever reason. So there are a lot of people who can be converted to bulls when FOMO kicks in which squeezes price higher. Then as the move becomes more exponential the cycle repeats until the move is over.I would suggest we are most likely looking for a scenario similar to the Yellow circles below.This will be a hated post because of where sentiment is right now which is another reason why I feel we are closing on this bottom. Negative sentiment at significant lows. Nothing is guaranteed but history often rhymes.

Now it got harder there are way more possible betas and only a few actually outperform (namely $PENDLE for $ETH for example).I dont think the game is over it just became a lil bit harder.People use $TAO as an example of main outperformance but actually for example both $KIZUNA and $MND (have somebody an opinion about Mind?) outperformed it lately.Another case is pre-market tokens now we have decent ways to bid them (@HyperliquidX @aevoxyz @kucoincom @WhalesMarket... you can pick your favorite flavor) but bidding beta in the couple days immediately before have been highly rewarding too.2) $GEAR - new Eigen beta?@GearboxProtocol today announced the best performing Eigen Points leverage maker (x9.5 is a fucking ton)Can it still a bit of the spotlight from $PENDLE?I think so but right now there are still a couple hiccups for the general public to access it which hopefully will go away soon (threshold + form + nft?).Gear also fits an interesting role the underperforming for long token with a good product (first Pure now applied to this) sort of like $GEL.3) $SYNO - Wormhole Beta?We dont know exactly when and how $W will hit the deck people rumour that well get something on the 21st or on the 28th but who knows.Anyway a couple projects are building directly on Wormhole: two lending markets and Mayan but only one (to my knowledge) has a token which is SYNO.Now it may be a bit early to bid but itll be what i follow as we receive more informations about $WOn the darker side lending platform tokens tend to vastly underperform so gotta be careful.4) $STRK - Finally tomorrow?Not sure what to expect devs are normally more cautious compared to normal users so probably theyll dump their allocations even though this might penalize them for STRK part 2.I think i may consider bidding STRK or beta if STRK doesnt dump at all or if it dumps A LOT.If its something in between then there are a lot of good opportunities in the market probably wont be worth to punt on this.FDV is high but also less relevant rn + in line with competitors.@tradeparadex is an interesting one to play on-chain.5) $ONDOThesis unchanged if anything empowered by current price action. Dont plan to get rid of the bag too soon still trying to grasp the concept of holding for longer and this will be my playground ig.6) $BLAST & $BLURWell kinda repeating the same concept i did for STRK W and others.A bid on $BLAST or on $BLUR (as beta same founder + staking) is not a bid on the project success but a bid on the attention marketshare that itll have in the next future.Its very simple: people want to bet they just have to decide what to bet on. Theyll bet on whatever gets the most attention in that moment.As we get closer to the launch this will expand.Is it better to long BLAST on Aevo or BLUR?Im doing the latter think its good enough with accessibility and also a potential NFT comeback led by Pengus (and possibly others) may help.Blast will also be interesting in terms of the dapps available on it there are several that are trying to position already to benefit from this situation like @sax_trade and @nftperp.The precise dates for Blast will be announced this week.7) $YUP: @farcaster_xyz and @LensProtocol Well attention kinda drawn away by AI right now but this will also be a recurrent theme this year or at least the first two quarters especially with @friendtech too cooking something with v2.0.In this case its not even about beta this is literally the only thing one can bid.8) $PANDORA: @Pandora_ERC404 I still like ERC404 despite selling Pandora too early and having to buy back ive always followed NFT tokenization in its various shapes quite closely (nftx sudo nftperp tribe insrt v1...) and especially considering how much attention gaming is getting this year erc404 is a particularly interesting thing.Is it life changing? No but were finally seeing new things being tried out.I was planning to talk about $META too but i totally missed it and it pumped quite a lot so dont feel like exploring more but go take a look at the design its quite interesting and people should experiment with variations on that.Thats all for today gn everybody.On a last note: ive just noticed i breached the 10k threshold thank you all for that.

tweet_text: no matter how much money you think you can make this cycle or how much you actually do make  no number is worth losing your longterm health over  short term sure i can get behind that its not unreasonable to go a few days on low sleep or to sit for 16hrs a day for a week if something insane is happening and youre in the zone  its not gonna kill you and probably wont shave any meaningful amount of time off your life or make the quality of your life worse  but if you spend 18 months hunkered in a dark room not leaving your chair not exercising not eating well not sleeping well its gonna really f you up  the kicker is that youre probably gonna make less money on average if you treat your body like shit because your brain is very much connected to your physical health and not eating well  sleeping well  exercising will almost surely mean youre making bad trades  bad financial decisions  take the time to go for a few 15 min walks per day   take the time to stretch  take the time to drink that extra glass of water  force yourself to sleep enough  youll be healthier and wealthier
tweet_raw: No matter how much money you think you can make this cycle or how much you actually do make -- no number is worth losing your long-term health overShort term sure I can get behind that. Its not unreasonable to go a few days on low sleep or to sit for 16hrs a day for a week if something insane is happening and youre in the zone.Its not gonna kill you and probably wont shave any meaningful amount of time off your life or make the quality of your life worse.But if you spend 18 months hunkered in a dark room not leaving your chair not exercising not eating well not sleeping well.. its gonna really F you up.The kicker is that youre probably gonna make *less* money on average if you treat your body like shit because your brain is very much connected to your physical health and not eating well / sleeping well / exercising will almost surely mean youre making bad trades / bad financial decisions.Take the time to go for a few 15 min walks per day. Take the time to stretch.Take the time to drink that extra glass of water.Force yourself to sleep enough.Youll be healthier AND wealthier.

tweet_text: polkadot parachain or ethereum l2  by the beginning of 2024 i can state the fact that the issue of ethereums development towards a multichain network has received a more or less clear trajectory what has not been for the last 5 years but only meant that ethereum is waiting for sharding  now i see that eth is not just starting to implement sharding but is striving to achieve a heterogeneous state by abandoning sharding in favor of supporting various forms and types of l2 therefore in the near future we will observe a multitude of appspecific l2 instead of multiple copies of l2 evm thus ethereum will now try to catch up with the current state of polkadot a state not just a multichain network but also heterogeneous by the nature of segments  from current observations i will share a couple of notes about what i like today in polkadot relative to ethereum l2 implementations   architecture collator  paravalidator  validatorfinalizers ethereum only has a role like collator and it is discussed in the topic decentralized sequencer  native data availability check mechanism when checking a block from collators paravalidators sow data into the internal data availability service and the validatorfinalizers separately check the availability of data before sealing the block ethereums data availability is hot right now but the architecture of solutions should be studied in practice closer to summer  xcm i consider crosschain transactions one of the most magical features of polkadot if polkadot can connect not through hrmp but directly parachains without a link with the relay chain it can turn out very cool the question of linking ethereum l2 segments i remember gavins presentation from copenhagen with embassies in the runtimes of parachains but we are waiting for implementation  but still its interesting personally  two projects very close to me are trying their own ways but whatever they do separately both ethereum and polkadot are moving in the same direction creating a multichain heterogeneous network to service the world computer
tweet_raw: Polkadot #Parachain or Ethereum #L2?By the beginning of 2024 I can state the fact that the issue of Ethereums development towards a multi-chain network has received a more or less clear trajectory. What has not been for the last 5 years but only meant that Ethereum is waiting for #shardingâ€¦Now I see that eth is not just starting to implement sharding but is striving to achieve a heterogeneous state by abandoning sharding in favor of supporting various forms and types of L2. Therefore in the near future we will observe a multitude of App-specific L2 instead of multiple copies of L2 EVM. Thus Ethereum will now try to catch up with the current state of Polkadot; a state not just a multi-chain network but also heterogeneous by the nature of segments.From current observations I will share a couple of notes about what I like today in Polkadot relative to Ethereum L2 implementations:- Architecture collator > para-validator > validator-finalizers. Ethereum only has a role like collator and it is discussed in the topic Decentralized #Sequencer- Native data availability check mechanism. When checking a block from collators para-validators sow data into the internal Data Availability Service. And the validator-finalizers separately check the availability of data before sealing the block. Ethereums Data Availability is hot right now but the architecture of solutions should be studied in practice closer to summer.- XCM. I consider cross-chain transactions one of the most magical features of Polkadot. If Polkadot can connect not through HRMP but directly parachains without a link with the Relay Chain it can turn out very cool! The question of linking Ethereum L2 segments. I remember Gavins presentation from Copenhagen with embassies in the runtimes of parachains but we are waiting for implementation.But still its interesting personally - two projects very close to me are trying their own ways but whatever they do separately both Ethereum and Polkadot are moving in the same direction creating a multi-chain heterogeneous network to service the world computer.

From the 5th day onwards he started to lose appetite and on the 10th day after start of symptoms he was dead. Just gone. Imagine. A much loved healthy senior person will be missing from the life of everyone in that family. Imagine the void.
